WEBVTT

01:44.311 --> 01:47.348
[GENTLE COUNTRY MUSIC
PLAYING OVER STEREO]

01:47.486 --> 01:49.488
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

01:49.626 --> 01:54.355
<i>♪ I used to think I found ♪</i>

01:54.493 --> 01:58.601
<i> </i><i>♪ My head must be in a cloud ♪</i>

01:59.912 --> 02:02.605
[OVEN DOOR CLANKING]

02:04.572 --> 02:08.783
<i> </i><i>♪ One who's always on my mind ♪</i>

02:08.921 --> 02:11.614
<i>♪ You are the one I love ♪</i>

02:11.752 --> 02:13.823
Well, you were right,
Daddy.

02:13.961 --> 02:15.307
It is the igniter.

02:18.862 --> 02:20.209
Okay.

02:20.347 --> 02:22.832
Just stop what you're doing
and let me look at it.

02:22.970 --> 02:23.867
All right?

02:26.215 --> 02:29.149
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

02:34.292 --> 02:38.261
[SUSPENSEFUL
ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PLAYING]

02:45.026 --> 02:47.305
[DOORS CLICKING]

02:54.829 --> 02:57.177
[DOOR CREAKING]

02:59.627 --> 03:01.871
Owen, hi.

03:07.290 --> 03:08.464
Evening, Clyde.

03:09.672 --> 03:11.501
We just closed up.

03:11.639 --> 03:13.538
[SIGHING]
Yeah, I know.

03:13.676 --> 03:16.126
Just making
a short business call.

03:16.265 --> 03:18.370
You know our parcel
arrives tomorrow.

03:19.509 --> 03:20.786
I'm gonna have to ask

03:20.924 --> 03:23.720
you be at the brewery
at the usual time.

03:23.858 --> 03:24.894
OWEN:
We're gonna be there.

03:26.447 --> 03:28.104
Well,
spread the word.

03:30.244 --> 03:34.386
Lena, look, I know
your heart isn't into this.

03:34.524 --> 03:38.079
Makes you feel dirty,
ashamed.

03:39.667 --> 03:42.532
So if you want
to forego your civil duties

03:42.670 --> 03:47.227
for tomorrow night,
I will grant you a free pass,

03:49.090 --> 03:51.783
take you back to my place,

03:51.921 --> 03:57.340
have a nice dinner,
then enjoy some time together.

03:57.478 --> 03:58.824
You better slow down, boy.

04:00.895 --> 04:02.000
[SCOFFING]

04:03.415 --> 04:04.554
You know,

04:06.556 --> 04:08.627
you and I
are gonna end up together

04:10.353 --> 04:12.079
whether you like it or not.
[GRUNTING]

04:12.217 --> 04:13.114
Clyde!

04:15.013 --> 04:15.945
Yes, Owen.

04:16.083 --> 04:17.878
I'm gonna ask you kindly

04:19.293 --> 04:21.157
to take your hands
off my daughter.

04:21.295 --> 04:24.505
[DRAMATIC
ORCHESTRAL THEME PLAYING]

04:24.643 --> 04:25.955
[SCOFFING]

04:28.854 --> 04:30.270
Now you know what, Owen?

04:30.408 --> 04:32.789
I am being disrespectful.

04:32.927 --> 04:33.790
OWEN:Yeah.

04:35.102 --> 04:36.172
My apologies.

04:37.656 --> 04:39.348
Ah, hell.

04:39.486 --> 04:41.246
You know me, Owen.

04:41.384 --> 04:44.456
I cross the line sometimes.

04:44.594 --> 04:47.390
Guess I gotta learn to be
a little more disciplined, huh?

04:48.978 --> 04:52.844
Now I think we both know that,
don't we?

04:52.982 --> 04:54.121
[GRUNTING]

04:54.259 --> 04:55.881
[CHAIR THUDDING]

04:56.019 --> 04:57.469
Daddy.

04:57.607 --> 04:58.953
Daddy.

04:59.091 --> 05:00.196
Are you okay?

05:00.334 --> 05:01.818
Look, I shouldn't
have done that.

05:01.956 --> 05:02.819
All right?

05:02.957 --> 05:04.959
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

05:05.097 --> 05:06.340
Let's go.

05:06.478 --> 05:09.032
[OWEN GROANING]

05:11.621 --> 05:14.175
Are you okay?

05:14.314 --> 05:16.523
[DRAMATIC
ORCHESTRAL THEME PLAYING]

05:16.661 --> 05:18.041
[DOOR THUDDING]

05:20.596 --> 05:24.151
[DRAMATIC
ORCHESTRAL THEME PLAYING]

05:27.637 --> 05:33.194
Brian, you said
you'd send an angel.

05:37.164 --> 05:39.028
If there was ever a time,

05:41.996 --> 05:43.135
it's now.

05:46.173 --> 05:49.970
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS THEME PLAYING]

05:52.110 --> 05:55.009
[SINGER VOCALIZING]

06:17.377 --> 06:21.277
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS THEME
CONTINUES]

07:18.161 --> 07:22.062
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS THEME
CONTINUES]

08:29.025 --> 08:30.613
[CANS THUDDING]

08:32.857 --> 08:34.997
[BELL RINGING]

08:40.036 --> 08:41.244
Afternoon.

08:41.382 --> 08:44.800
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

08:44.938 --> 08:46.353
Afternoon.

08:51.945 --> 08:55.086
Been walking
for quite a while.

08:56.363 --> 08:57.985
I'm kind of hungry.

08:58.123 --> 09:01.886
I'm, uh--
I'm strapped for funds,

09:02.024 --> 09:03.301
but, uh, I'm pretty handy.

09:03.439 --> 09:05.130
I thought if you had
any jobs need doing,

09:05.268 --> 09:07.961
well, maybe I could
earn myself a meal.

09:08.099 --> 09:09.065
You're a vet.

09:10.446 --> 09:12.621
In that case,
meal's on the house.

09:12.759 --> 09:14.139
That's very kind of you,

09:14.277 --> 09:16.935
but I'd just as soon
earn my meal.

09:17.073 --> 09:18.730
It's not a handout,
it's a gift.

09:18.868 --> 09:20.111
I understand,

09:20.249 --> 09:22.354
but all the same to you,
I'll do the work.

09:24.356 --> 09:28.568
Well, I got a broken shelf
over here.

09:30.362 --> 09:31.467
I'd have fixed it myself,

09:31.605 --> 09:33.434
but my eyes
ain't what they used to be.

09:34.781 --> 09:36.541
Yeah, well,

09:36.679 --> 09:38.647
that doesn't look
like it'll be a problem.

09:38.785 --> 09:40.856
Well then, we got a deal. Heh.

09:40.994 --> 09:42.236
Name's Vernon.

09:43.962 --> 09:44.825
Vernon.

09:49.968 --> 09:52.695
So you traveling through?

09:52.833 --> 09:53.731
That's right.

09:55.249 --> 09:56.941
That would be
my recommendation.

09:59.012 --> 10:00.013
Why is that?

10:00.151 --> 10:02.187
Not safe here for outsiders.

10:02.325 --> 10:04.258
I suggest you head
further north.

10:05.294 --> 10:07.054
Why north?

10:07.192 --> 10:08.090
Or south.

10:09.332 --> 10:10.644
Just anywhere
but here.

10:10.782 --> 10:11.645
Trust me.

10:12.819 --> 10:15.718
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

10:36.428 --> 10:40.329
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

10:46.853 --> 10:48.164
[CAR DOOR CLICKING]

10:48.302 --> 10:50.546
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

10:50.684 --> 10:53.653
[BELL RINGING]

10:55.068 --> 10:59.072
Sheriff Wiley,
what can I do for you today?

10:59.210 --> 11:00.763
WILEY:
So who do we have here?

11:00.901 --> 11:03.145
VERNON:
He's, uh, just passing through.

11:03.283 --> 11:04.387
Is that right?

11:10.324 --> 11:13.673
Well, good afternoon.

11:14.535 --> 11:15.882
Afternoon.

11:16.641 --> 11:18.056
So, uh,

11:18.194 --> 11:20.714
Vernon tells me
you're passing through.

11:24.787 --> 11:26.064
I haven't decided yet.

11:27.859 --> 11:31.035
Well, heh,
let me decide for you.

11:31.173 --> 11:33.727
Now we don't care much
for outsiders here

11:33.865 --> 11:36.212
in our quiet little town.

11:36.350 --> 11:38.939
So why don't you
just finish up that meal

11:39.077 --> 11:40.561
and find your way
out of Rondo.

11:42.046 --> 11:42.943
Clear?

11:47.499 --> 11:48.811
Let me ask you, Sheriff,

11:48.949 --> 11:50.951
am I breaking
some kind of law?

11:51.089 --> 11:52.263
[CHUCKLES]

11:55.197 --> 11:57.061
I can be real inventive.

12:00.581 --> 12:02.652
Special Forces, huh?

12:02.791 --> 12:04.689
Well, just 'cause
you're a war veteran,

12:04.827 --> 12:07.657
don't mean you get any
special treatment around here.

12:10.660 --> 12:11.869
Yeah.

12:12.007 --> 12:14.423
I'll pick up the tab for you,
my friend.

12:14.561 --> 12:15.942
You have a good trip now.

12:17.875 --> 12:20.878
That one's on me there, Vernon.

12:21.016 --> 12:22.362
[CLEARS THROAT]

12:22.500 --> 12:25.054
[BELL RINGING]

12:27.608 --> 12:29.300
[CAR DOOR CLICKING]

12:29.438 --> 12:30.888
[ENGINE STARTS]

12:31.026 --> 12:34.892
[BEETHOVEN'S "MOONLIGHT SONATA"
PLAYING ON PIANO]

12:42.969 --> 12:43.935
Hey, Dad.

12:45.972 --> 12:46.835
Yeah?

12:48.906 --> 12:50.321
CLYDE:
Just heading out to the brewery.

12:50.459 --> 12:52.426
I want to see
if you needed anything.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.429
Just keep
your eyes and ears open.

12:55.567 --> 12:57.915
All right, see you later.

12:59.813 --> 13:02.643
[RESUMES PLAYING
"MOONLIGHT SONATA"]

13:02.782 --> 13:04.128
[DOOR CLICKING]

13:04.266 --> 13:07.131
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

13:08.097 --> 13:10.962
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

13:22.146 --> 13:24.838
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

13:28.738 --> 13:31.638
["MOONLIGHT SONATA" CONTINUES]

13:41.993 --> 13:44.547
[GATE CLATTERING]

13:46.411 --> 13:49.138
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

13:53.660 --> 13:55.869
MAN:
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

14:02.393 --> 14:03.497
Let's go, quicker.

14:04.844 --> 14:06.362
MAN:
Come on, hurry up.

14:08.330 --> 14:11.022
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

14:13.818 --> 14:16.234
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

14:16.372 --> 14:18.823
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

14:22.068 --> 14:22.965
Randall.

14:24.484 --> 14:25.381
Let's go.

14:26.935 --> 14:28.833
Jeremiah wants
to have a word with you.

14:30.662 --> 14:32.526
What are you gonna do
to my husband?

14:33.562 --> 14:34.494
Get in.

14:38.187 --> 14:39.085
Come on, go.

14:41.915 --> 14:43.710
Let's go,
back to work.

14:43.848 --> 14:45.401
Come on.

14:45.539 --> 14:47.403
Go. Quicker.
[ENGINE STARTS]

14:47.541 --> 14:50.234
[GATE CLATTERING]

14:54.203 --> 14:56.826
[ENGINE REVVING]

14:58.656 --> 15:01.555
[DRAMATIC ORCHESTRAL
THEME PLAYING]

15:24.613 --> 15:27.202
[DOOR CREAKING]

15:36.625 --> 15:38.592
Hello.
Hello.

15:38.730 --> 15:41.664
I'd like a room for the night.
How much?

15:42.596 --> 15:44.081
We're, uh...

15:44.219 --> 15:46.324
We're a little filled up
at the moment.

15:54.263 --> 15:56.541
I'd like a room for the night.

15:56.679 --> 15:58.302
How much?

15:58.440 --> 15:59.889
[GULPS]

16:01.477 --> 16:04.239
It'll be, uh,
be $20 a night.

16:04.377 --> 16:06.172
That's fine.

16:06.310 --> 16:08.968
Save a room for me.
I'll be back.

16:09.106 --> 16:10.452
CLERK:
Yes, sir.

16:10.590 --> 16:12.695
[DOOR CLICKING]

16:12.833 --> 16:15.733
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

16:18.701 --> 16:21.290
[DOORS CLICKING]

16:31.335 --> 16:35.201
[GENTLE
ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PLAYING]

16:41.276 --> 16:44.555
Mr. Whitfield.
Randall "The Scandal."

16:44.693 --> 16:47.489
What have I done?
I think you know.

16:47.627 --> 16:49.491
I don't know
what you're talking about.

16:49.629 --> 16:52.390
You broke the cardinal rule
of our relationship.

16:54.427 --> 16:57.947
I received a call this morning
from our attorney general.

16:58.086 --> 17:01.468
Said his office
had been receiving

17:01.606 --> 17:04.437
unsettling news
about our activities.

17:06.059 --> 17:07.923
Make this easy on yourself.

17:10.857 --> 17:13.549
Yes, it's true--
I made the call,

17:13.687 --> 17:17.036
but my wife Vivian,
she's so scared.

17:17.174 --> 17:19.659
She begged me to call.

17:19.797 --> 17:25.872
Behind every great man is
a woman with blood on her hands.

17:26.010 --> 17:27.839
Regardless
of who made you do it,

17:27.977 --> 17:30.187
the actions were your own.

17:30.325 --> 17:32.603
Please, Mr. Whitfield.

17:32.741 --> 17:34.708
I promise it won't happen again.

17:34.846 --> 17:36.572
You right or left-handed?

17:39.403 --> 17:40.887
[SUSPENSEFUL
ORCHESTRAL THEME PLAYING]

17:41.025 --> 17:43.855
[BONE SNAPPING]
[RANDALL SCREAMING]

17:43.993 --> 17:45.374
Remember this.

17:47.411 --> 17:50.276
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

17:50.414 --> 17:52.795
[DOG BARKING]

18:02.633 --> 18:04.359
[SOFT COUNTRY MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

18:04.497 --> 18:06.257
[DOOR CLICKING]

18:16.164 --> 18:19.753
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

18:19.891 --> 18:22.239
Well, we got a guest.

18:23.516 --> 18:24.413
Afternoon.

18:25.725 --> 18:27.727
OWEN:
What can I do for you?

18:27.865 --> 18:29.625
I'm passing through.

18:29.763 --> 18:32.007
I thought
I might spend the night.

18:32.145 --> 18:33.595
I'm short on cash,

18:33.733 --> 18:36.253
so I thought if you got
any odd jobs need doing,

18:36.391 --> 18:38.772
I'm pretty handy.

18:38.910 --> 18:42.121
I'm just looking to earn a day's
pay, then I'll move on.

18:42.259 --> 18:43.432
Where are you headed?

18:43.570 --> 18:44.675
Nowhere in particular.

18:44.813 --> 18:46.125
Ah, nomada.

18:47.402 --> 18:49.162
Sorry?
A nomad.

18:49.300 --> 18:50.750
No-- Oh.

18:57.515 --> 18:59.379
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

19:01.381 --> 19:03.038
My son-in-law
was Special Forces.

19:04.557 --> 19:05.696
Sergeant.

19:05.834 --> 19:07.525
He lost his life in combat.

19:07.663 --> 19:09.286
Very sorry to hear that.

19:12.358 --> 19:14.567
You know anything
about oven igniters?

19:16.741 --> 19:18.226
I believe I do, yeah.

19:18.364 --> 19:20.159
I got one back here
giving me fits.

19:21.677 --> 19:23.679
You fix it
and I'll keep you on for a day.

19:23.817 --> 19:25.164
How's that for a deal?

19:26.751 --> 19:27.614
Deal.

19:27.752 --> 19:28.822
Owen Hayes.

19:28.960 --> 19:30.134
Owen.

19:32.619 --> 19:34.000
[SIGHS]
Lead the way.

19:35.795 --> 19:38.694
[METAL CLACKING]

19:44.113 --> 19:45.322
Oh, hey baby.

19:45.460 --> 19:46.806
This is my daughter, Lena.

19:46.944 --> 19:48.704
Lena, this is, um--

19:48.842 --> 19:50.223
You know, I didn't even
get your name.

19:52.467 --> 19:54.054
What was it you called me?

19:54.193 --> 19:55.470
[CHUCKLES]
Nomada.

19:56.678 --> 19:58.197
Nomada.

19:58.335 --> 19:59.784
That'll do.

19:59.922 --> 20:00.854
Hi.

20:03.236 --> 20:04.341
Let's talk.

20:07.447 --> 20:10.692
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

20:13.108 --> 20:15.110
OWEN:
Hey.

20:15.248 --> 20:16.870
LENA:
What are you doing, Daddy?

20:17.008 --> 20:18.631
The man's in need, Lena.

20:18.769 --> 20:19.735
And so are we.

20:21.185 --> 20:22.255
And if he can fix our oven,

20:22.393 --> 20:24.084
I'm gonna keep him on for a day.

20:24.223 --> 20:26.155
There's a lot
he can do around here.

20:26.294 --> 20:28.123
We don't know
anything about him.

20:29.573 --> 20:31.057
What if he's dangerous?

20:31.195 --> 20:32.748
He's not dangerous.

20:32.886 --> 20:35.026
The first sign of danger,
his ass is outta here.

20:35.164 --> 20:36.062
I promise you.

20:38.513 --> 20:40.204
This is a bad idea.

20:41.516 --> 20:44.622
He is gonna
be trouble for us.

20:44.760 --> 20:47.142
You let me deal with that.
Okay?

20:47.280 --> 20:48.661
But if you don't--
[SOFT CLATTER]

20:48.799 --> 20:51.250
If you don't feel safe,
you just keep your distance.

20:52.803 --> 20:53.907
Oh, I will.

20:58.429 --> 21:01.294
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS THEME PLAYING]

21:45.131 --> 21:46.166
[SOFTLY]
Whew!

21:54.174 --> 21:56.522
[LIQUID SPRAYING]

21:56.660 --> 21:58.593
[MATCH STRIKING]

22:00.871 --> 22:03.252
[FIRE WHOOSHING]

22:03.391 --> 22:05.496
Yes. There you go.

22:12.814 --> 22:14.022
[DOOR THUDDING]

22:14.160 --> 22:16.852
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

22:22.686 --> 22:26.103
[WHEELCHAIR CREAKING]

22:26.241 --> 22:27.380
[DOOR CREAKING]

22:27.518 --> 22:29.900
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

22:31.384 --> 22:32.281
Clyde.

22:36.458 --> 22:37.390
Owen.

22:37.528 --> 22:38.874
[DOOR CLICKING]

22:39.841 --> 22:41.843
Well now,

22:41.981 --> 22:44.501
who in the hell
do we have here?

22:46.157 --> 22:49.229
This is, uh, Nomada.

22:50.299 --> 22:51.197
Nomada?

22:53.372 --> 22:55.270
What in the hell kind of name
is Nomada?

22:56.996 --> 22:58.791
OWEN:
He's just passing through town,

22:58.929 --> 23:00.482
helping me out
with a few things.

23:01.690 --> 23:02.553
CLYDE:
Is he now?

23:04.417 --> 23:06.695
So Nomada,

23:08.317 --> 23:10.423
what the hell brings you
all the way out here?

23:12.321 --> 23:14.772
Like the man said,
just passing through.

23:14.910 --> 23:17.257
CLYDE: Is that right?
OWEN: He's here for a day.

23:17.396 --> 23:19.156
He's just helping me
with some odd jobs.

23:19.294 --> 23:20.813
Yeah?

23:20.951 --> 23:21.883
Who says?

23:22.884 --> 23:26.094
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

23:26.232 --> 23:29.615
There's so many things I
can't do in this chair, Clyde.

23:29.753 --> 23:30.857
The man's handy.

23:30.995 --> 23:32.445
He's already fixed the oven.

23:37.416 --> 23:38.865
Just for the day.

23:40.867 --> 23:43.767
Then I think it's best
you be on your way.

23:43.905 --> 23:45.769
[METAL CLACKS]

23:48.875 --> 23:51.257
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

24:00.508 --> 24:02.751
You should join us
for a drink, Lena.

24:02.889 --> 24:03.752
Take a break.

24:05.133 --> 24:08.136
Yeah, Clyde, please.

24:08.274 --> 24:09.965
Ah, come on.

24:10.103 --> 24:13.037
I just want to talk to you
for five minutes,

24:13.175 --> 24:14.453
just a little.

24:16.006 --> 24:17.317
I don't think so.

24:18.422 --> 24:19.319
Okay.

24:20.459 --> 24:23.669
Oh, Lena, one last thing.

24:23.807 --> 24:26.188
I don't really like
being told no.

24:26.326 --> 24:27.811
Kind of hurts my feelings.

24:29.778 --> 24:33.161
[TENSE THEME CONTINUES]

24:37.510 --> 24:40.479
[SOFT COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

24:42.481 --> 24:45.449
No. No, no, I've had plenty.
Thanks.

24:54.113 --> 24:55.010
Good food, huh?

24:56.115 --> 24:57.668
Very good. Yeah.

24:57.806 --> 25:02.328
Thank you for inviting me
to sit down with you.

25:07.540 --> 25:11.855
Tell me, those men
who came by here today--

25:11.993 --> 25:13.753
- Yeah.
- -who are they?

25:13.891 --> 25:15.514
That's Whitfield's goons.

25:15.652 --> 25:17.585
Jeremiah Whitfield.

25:17.723 --> 25:19.690
He owns this town
and everybody in it.

25:19.828 --> 25:21.934
Little smart-ass kid,
that's Clyde.

25:22.072 --> 25:23.073
That's Jeremiah's son.

25:24.557 --> 25:25.903
He's the one who's taking

25:26.041 --> 25:28.112
a particular liking
to you, Lena?

25:28.250 --> 25:29.769
Feeling is not mutual.

25:29.907 --> 25:32.047
It's something we've been
dealing with for a while.

25:32.185 --> 25:35.016
And I can take care of myself.

25:35.154 --> 25:36.327
Excuse me.

25:36.465 --> 25:38.364
Let's just hope
it don't come to that.

25:40.711 --> 25:41.574
I gotta tell you.

25:43.024 --> 25:44.957
I don't like it here.

25:45.095 --> 25:48.270
I don't feel safe for me,
and I don't feel safe for her.

25:48.408 --> 25:49.548
So why don't you get out?

25:50.583 --> 25:51.998
Because I can't.

26:00.835 --> 26:04.701
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

26:04.839 --> 26:06.047
[SIGHS]

26:08.256 --> 26:09.188
Nomada.

26:10.016 --> 26:12.674
Um, this is--

26:12.812 --> 26:14.642
This is for you.

26:16.920 --> 26:19.681
Thank you.
You-you do good work.

26:19.819 --> 26:20.958
Thank you.

26:22.408 --> 26:25.169
Uh, but the-the thing is,
we're in a--

26:25.307 --> 26:27.275
We're in
a precarious situation here,

26:27.413 --> 26:32.280
and your being here
actually makes things worse,

26:33.315 --> 26:35.352
so I'm asking you

26:36.733 --> 26:38.597
don't come back, okay?

26:38.735 --> 26:41.116
[THUNDER CRASHING]

26:41.254 --> 26:42.773
It's-it's nothing personal.

26:42.911 --> 26:44.741
It's just, ahem,
the way things are.

26:44.879 --> 26:46.570
I understand.

26:46.708 --> 26:47.882
[SUCKS TEETH]

26:50.609 --> 26:51.886
Thanks again.

26:57.201 --> 26:58.133
Good luck.

26:58.271 --> 27:01.102
[THUNDER CRASHING]

27:04.968 --> 27:07.798
[DRAMATIC ORCHESTRAL
THEME PLAYING]

27:07.936 --> 27:09.179
[DOOR CLICKING]

27:09.317 --> 27:12.665
[THUNDER RUMBLING]
[DOOR OPENS]

27:12.803 --> 27:15.185
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY]

27:24.056 --> 27:25.782
[BELL RINGS]

27:29.578 --> 27:32.685
Twenty bucks.
I'll take that room now.

27:32.823 --> 27:35.446
Yeah, number three.
Upstairs on the left.

27:35.584 --> 27:38.415
Bathroom's
right across the hall.

27:38.553 --> 27:40.900
Hey, do you need any towels?

27:41.038 --> 27:44.352
It's $5,
refundable upon checkout.

27:46.872 --> 27:49.771
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

27:54.362 --> 27:55.294
Five dollars.

27:57.330 --> 27:58.228
Thanks.

28:01.300 --> 28:04.165
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY]

28:08.169 --> 28:12.000
[THUNDER CRASHING]
[RAIN PATTERING]

28:15.832 --> 28:19.698
[THUNDER CRASHING]
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

28:23.253 --> 28:25.220
[THUNDER CRASHING]

28:33.539 --> 28:34.885
RESIDENT:
Careful.

28:37.232 --> 28:40.097
[THUNDER CRASHING]

28:44.757 --> 28:47.587
[THUNDER CRASHING]

28:50.176 --> 28:52.592
[THUNDER CRASHING]

28:52.731 --> 28:53.628
Careful.

28:59.427 --> 29:02.568
[THUNDER CRASHING]

29:02.706 --> 29:04.743
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

29:06.227 --> 29:09.989
[GUNS FIRING]
[SOLDIERS SCREAMING]

29:10.127 --> 29:12.820
[THUNDER CRASHING]

29:12.958 --> 29:15.477
[GUNS FIRING]

29:20.413 --> 29:23.106
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

29:23.244 --> 29:26.247
You led us into an ambush,
it was--

29:26.385 --> 29:28.490
[GUN FIRING]

29:28.628 --> 29:30.803
[GUNS FIRING]

29:32.771 --> 29:34.496
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

29:34.634 --> 29:37.154
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

29:39.156 --> 29:41.780
[EXPLOSION BOOMING]

29:43.333 --> 29:45.853
[GUNS FIRING]

29:45.991 --> 29:47.647
[MAN GROANING]

29:50.754 --> 29:52.998
[SIGHING]

29:56.898 --> 29:58.831
[SINGER VOCALIZING]

29:58.969 --> 30:02.283
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS THEME PLAYING]

30:11.395 --> 30:13.501
[GROANING]

30:17.470 --> 30:19.818
[THUNDER CRASHING]

30:21.578 --> 30:25.478
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS
THEME CONTINUES]

30:32.520 --> 30:35.178
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

30:55.715 --> 30:58.649
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

31:02.412 --> 31:05.242
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

31:06.381 --> 31:07.382
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS THEME PLAYING]

31:07.520 --> 31:09.315
I'm gonna need the ladder.

31:13.975 --> 31:16.875
[GENTLE BLUEGRASS
THEME CONTINUES]

31:21.258 --> 31:22.156
Morning.

31:27.851 --> 31:28.748
Hmm.

31:30.129 --> 31:31.027
Good.

31:38.068 --> 31:40.346
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

31:40.484 --> 31:42.314
The damn place
is falling apart, Lena.

31:42.452 --> 31:45.179
There's so much
that man can do in one day.

31:45.317 --> 31:47.146
That's all I'm asking for
is one more day.

31:47.284 --> 31:48.423
It is a mistake.

31:48.561 --> 31:50.425
I'll take responsibility, okay?

31:50.563 --> 31:52.496
I can make them understand.

31:52.634 --> 31:55.258
You saw what they did
to Randall, Daddy.

31:55.396 --> 31:57.260
I don't want you to get hurt,

31:57.398 --> 32:00.435
and you're putting our welfare
into the hands of a stranger.

32:01.747 --> 32:03.369
It's not worth it.

32:04.301 --> 32:05.406
You listen to me, Lena.

32:07.028 --> 32:09.444
I'm willing to take that chance.

32:10.790 --> 32:11.895
To what end?

32:15.071 --> 32:17.936
[SIGN BUZZING]

32:20.593 --> 32:21.974
[TOOLBOX THUDS]

32:25.978 --> 32:29.499
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

32:29.637 --> 32:32.329
Wow. You know,
that looks really good.

32:32.467 --> 32:36.023
Well, good enough anyway.

32:36.161 --> 32:39.888
Yeah, there's a lot of stuff
that can be done around here

32:40.027 --> 32:41.649
if you don't mind
sticking around.

32:42.788 --> 32:43.685
All right.

32:43.823 --> 32:45.377
I can give you a day or two.

32:45.515 --> 32:46.447
No problem.

32:49.864 --> 32:50.969
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

32:56.353 --> 32:58.838
[GRUNTING]

33:00.944 --> 33:02.773
Why are you still here,
Nomada?

33:05.155 --> 33:06.536
I asked you to leave.

33:06.674 --> 33:08.814
Your father's a good man.

33:08.952 --> 33:11.851
I'm just helping him out, huh?

33:11.990 --> 33:14.509
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

33:16.753 --> 33:19.169
I'll be gone soon enough.

33:19.307 --> 33:20.239
I promise.

33:20.377 --> 33:22.207
[CAR DOORS CLICKING]

33:26.659 --> 33:28.489
[DOOR CLICKING]

33:28.627 --> 33:30.077
Afternoon, Lena.

33:31.975 --> 33:33.252
Clyde.

33:33.390 --> 33:36.186
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

33:39.810 --> 33:41.640
Lena, you mind telling me

33:41.778 --> 33:43.573
why this son of a bitch
is still here.

33:45.575 --> 33:48.612
OWEN:
He's fixing a few more things around here, Clyde.

33:48.750 --> 33:50.890
The damn place is falling apart.

33:51.029 --> 33:52.927
I don't give a goddamn,
Owen.

33:53.065 --> 33:55.171
Now I gave you a direct order.

33:58.208 --> 34:00.693
You think I'm scared of you,
old man?

34:00.831 --> 34:02.385
Hmm?

34:02.523 --> 34:04.870
You got some nerve,
I'll say that.

34:05.008 --> 34:08.218
Clyde, I--
CLYDE: Stay out of this, Lena.

34:08.356 --> 34:11.601
You know what, I'm gonna
make this real simple.

34:13.396 --> 34:15.881
Now you got five minutes
to pack your shit

34:16.019 --> 34:18.677
and get the hell
out of this town.

34:18.815 --> 34:20.334
I suggest you comply.

34:22.198 --> 34:23.061
We clear?

34:25.201 --> 34:26.478
Good.

34:26.616 --> 34:29.584
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

34:35.211 --> 34:38.076
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

34:43.495 --> 34:48.948
Clyde, um, we don't ask
for much. You know that.

34:49.087 --> 34:54.092
So, um, my daddy just needs
his help for another day.

34:54.230 --> 34:55.472
I already just told you no.

34:56.922 --> 34:57.923
Well,
I'm asking you nicely.

34:58.061 --> 34:59.027
Goddamn it, Lena.

34:59.166 --> 35:00.822
What did I just say?

35:00.960 --> 35:02.238
Now you know the rules.

35:02.376 --> 35:03.446
I know, but--
What the hell has got--

35:03.584 --> 35:05.310
Clyde!
Shut your mouth.

35:05.448 --> 35:06.759
LENA:
Seriously, you are making a big deal

35:06.897 --> 35:08.106
out of nothing, Clyde.

35:08.244 --> 35:09.762
You know what?
Now you're hurting me, so--

35:09.900 --> 35:11.661
I just told you--
You don't tell me what to do.

35:11.799 --> 35:13.180
LENA:
You are hurting me.

35:13.318 --> 35:14.595
[BEER SPLASHING]

35:14.733 --> 35:16.873
[SUSPENSEFUL
ORCHESTRAL THEME PLAYING]

35:17.011 --> 35:19.117
[CLYDE GRUNTING]
[HAND SMACKING]

35:19.255 --> 35:21.567
[GRUNTING]

35:21.705 --> 35:22.844
[GUN FIRING]

35:22.982 --> 35:24.432
[BOTH GRUNTING]

35:24.570 --> 35:25.640
Clear your weapons.

35:25.778 --> 35:27.125
Put 'em on the table.

35:28.609 --> 35:30.507
CLYDE [GRUNTING]:
Do it. Do it now.

35:32.337 --> 35:33.648
Turn and walk outta here.

35:34.891 --> 35:38.722
You are so dead.
[GRUNTING]

35:38.860 --> 35:42.968
You ain't gonna live
out the day. [GRUNTING]

35:43.106 --> 35:44.625
You know who I am?

35:44.763 --> 35:46.040
[DOOR SLAMS]

35:48.387 --> 35:50.320
What's going on here?

35:56.188 --> 36:00.054
We help consolidate the cocaine,
weigh it, package it,

36:00.192 --> 36:02.850
and in exchange,
we're given the essentials.

36:02.988 --> 36:04.645
We are paid for our silence.

36:04.783 --> 36:07.199
And you can't leave?

36:07.337 --> 36:11.065
Well, we could,
but the Whitfields are networked

36:11.203 --> 36:12.929
with syndicates
across the country,

36:13.067 --> 36:15.173
so they'll find us
and they'll kill us.

36:15.311 --> 36:17.002
It's happened many times before.

36:18.176 --> 36:19.177
We know too much.

36:20.626 --> 36:23.008
OWEN:
Look, when my wife died,

36:23.146 --> 36:25.321
I actually found a way
to get Lena out of here.

36:27.564 --> 36:30.188
Of course the results,
I wound in this damn wheelchair.

36:30.326 --> 36:33.881
Then Brian dies and Lena just
come back to take care of me.

36:34.019 --> 36:36.470
[SIGHING]
And the sheriff,

36:36.608 --> 36:38.575
where does he fit in?

36:38.713 --> 36:39.576
He's in on it.

36:41.406 --> 36:43.477
LENA:
Look, I know your intentions were good,

36:43.615 --> 36:46.065
but what you started here today,

36:46.204 --> 36:48.620
about to get a whole lot worse.

36:51.726 --> 36:52.900
Owen, you got a safe?

36:53.728 --> 36:54.729
I do.

36:54.867 --> 36:58.043
Well, let's stow
these firearms.

36:59.562 --> 37:02.427
[WHEELCHAIR CLATTERING]

37:03.842 --> 37:05.913
[ENGINE REVVING]

37:06.051 --> 37:09.227
[TIRES SCREECHING]

37:09.365 --> 37:12.437
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

37:12.575 --> 37:15.233
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

37:23.241 --> 37:26.140
[CAR DOORS CLICKING]

37:30.178 --> 37:33.078
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

37:35.460 --> 37:38.117
[DOOR CLICKING]

37:38.256 --> 37:39.360
CLYDE:
Dad.

37:39.498 --> 37:41.120
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

37:43.813 --> 37:45.193
What the hell happened to you?

37:46.988 --> 37:48.680
We need to talk.

37:48.818 --> 37:50.716
We've got a serious problem.

37:50.854 --> 37:53.892
There's a stranger in town,
some crazy ass old man.

37:54.030 --> 37:55.583
Owen's taken him in.
Oh?

37:56.481 --> 37:58.137
He's trouble, Dad.

37:58.276 --> 38:01.831
Took our guns, threw our asses
outta the goddamn saloon.

38:07.837 --> 38:12.462
So some crazy old man
took your guns

38:12.600 --> 38:14.775
and threw the three of you
out of the saloon?

38:15.948 --> 38:17.260
One man?

38:19.504 --> 38:21.195
[SNIFFING]
I'll handle it.

38:21.333 --> 38:23.853
You stay the hell out of this.
Whoa, hold on.

38:23.991 --> 38:26.649
We don't need an incident
right now.

38:26.787 --> 38:28.789
Sheriff Wiley can handle this.

38:32.068 --> 38:34.622
[PHONE RINGING]

38:42.181 --> 38:43.390
Sheriff Wiley.

38:43.528 --> 38:45.081
Sheriff, Jeremiah.

38:45.219 --> 38:46.910
WILEY:
<i>What can I do for you?</i>

38:47.048 --> 38:49.534
Listen, we got some yokel
over at the Horseshoe.

38:49.672 --> 38:51.881
Clyde and his pals
got into fight with him

38:52.019 --> 38:53.434
and he took their guns.

38:53.572 --> 38:55.436
<i>Ah, shit.</i>

38:55.574 --> 38:57.680
I told
that Special Forces asshole

38:57.818 --> 38:59.060
to leave town yesterday.

38:59.198 --> 39:00.786
Get him outta town.
[WILEY SIGHS]

39:00.924 --> 39:02.892
<i>I'll take care of that</i>
<i>right now, Mr. Whitfield.</i>

39:03.030 --> 39:03.927
Thank you.

39:06.861 --> 39:08.207
Goddamn it.

39:08.346 --> 39:11.141
Get cleaned up
and get over to the brewery.

39:11.279 --> 39:12.246
Pull the car around.

39:14.213 --> 39:16.906
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

39:17.044 --> 39:19.771
This man instigated something
that will no doubt escalate.

39:19.909 --> 39:22.187
He's put us all
in a lot of danger.

39:22.325 --> 39:23.533
Yeah.
Well, maybe this is the time

39:23.671 --> 39:26.018
to take a stand,
do something finally.

39:26.156 --> 39:28.124
Yeah.
What can we do?

39:28.262 --> 39:30.678
There's nowhere we can go
where they can't find us.

39:30.816 --> 39:34.199
Besides, we're all
accessories to a crime.

39:34.337 --> 39:37.098
We could end up dead
or-or in prison.

39:37.236 --> 39:38.376
Hm.

39:39.998 --> 39:42.897
You know, Sam's right,
we are defenseless,

39:43.035 --> 39:45.624
but this man
was an ex-Green Beret.

39:47.385 --> 39:49.973
Maybe he knows someone
that can help us.

39:50.111 --> 39:52.769
The guy wouldn't be a bum
if he knew the right people.

39:52.907 --> 39:54.288
He needs to go.

39:54.426 --> 39:56.083
WOMAN:
Well, I wanna talk to him.

39:57.740 --> 39:58.603
We will.

40:02.054 --> 40:04.471
[LINE RINGING]

40:04.609 --> 40:06.783
MAN [OVER PHONE]: <i>Yeah?</i>
Hello, old friend.

40:08.129 --> 40:10.373
You recognize this voice?

40:10.511 --> 40:15.413
<i>Who is this?</i>
A ghost from your past.

40:15.551 --> 40:17.622
<i>Wait, is this a joke?</i>

40:19.071 --> 40:23.006
No, I've never been one
much for jokes.

40:23.144 --> 40:25.906
Matter of fact,
I remember you telling me

40:26.044 --> 40:28.426
I was about as funny
as a dead kitten.

40:29.772 --> 40:32.637
That hurt.
<i>No, this can't be.</i>

40:32.775 --> 40:34.604
<i>I was at your funeral.</i>

40:34.742 --> 40:36.434
<i> </i><i>We can't be speaking right now.</i>

40:36.572 --> 40:39.402
Yeah, but we are.
<i>Where are you?</i>

40:39.540 --> 40:42.301
I'm in a town called Rondo.

40:42.440 --> 40:45.235
And a world of pain
is about to hit this town,

40:45.373 --> 40:47.617
so I'm gonna need
to call in my marker.

40:49.377 --> 40:52.795
I'd say you owe me that.
<i>Anything, anything at all.</i>

40:52.933 --> 40:53.796
<i>Just ask.</i>

40:55.245 --> 40:57.800
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

40:59.491 --> 41:01.010
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

41:01.148 --> 41:02.529
[DOOR CLICKING]

41:02.667 --> 41:03.840
[CHATTER STOPS]

41:03.978 --> 41:05.117
[DOOR CLOSES]

41:06.774 --> 41:09.052
What the hell's going on here?

41:09.190 --> 41:11.365
Town meeting, is this?

41:11.503 --> 41:13.401
Hmm?

41:13.540 --> 41:15.990
You were warned, Randall.

41:16.128 --> 41:18.268
LENA:
Look, Sheriff, there's nothing going on here.

41:18.406 --> 41:19.615
We were just talking.

41:19.753 --> 41:20.616
About what?

41:22.031 --> 41:25.862
What you all
be talking about, huh?

41:26.000 --> 41:28.278
We're just planning
a little gathering for Daddy.

41:28.416 --> 41:29.521
It's his birthday.

41:29.659 --> 41:31.316
Is that right?Yeah.

41:31.454 --> 41:33.042
[CHUCKLES]

41:33.180 --> 41:36.217
Well, let me put it straight
to you right here, right now.

41:36.355 --> 41:38.392
There won't be no gathering.

41:40.152 --> 41:42.465
I want that son of a bitch
out here right now.

41:42.603 --> 41:43.742
Why?

41:43.880 --> 41:45.019
Because I'm putting him
under arrest.

41:45.157 --> 41:46.055
That's why.

41:47.159 --> 41:48.298
For what?

41:48.436 --> 41:50.404
Assault and battery,
Clyde and his boys.

41:50.542 --> 41:53.165
[SCOFFS]
Listen, Sheriff, he--

41:53.303 --> 41:54.960
Clyde struck my daughter.

41:55.098 --> 41:56.962
Shut up, Owen.
You shut that mouth

41:57.100 --> 41:59.724
or I'll arrest both of you
for harboring a fugitive.

41:59.862 --> 42:02.520
Now you gonna bring him
out here or what?

42:05.971 --> 42:06.869
Huh?

42:09.596 --> 42:11.563
Whoa, whoa, whoa, Sheriff.

42:11.701 --> 42:13.289
Sheriff, I'm sorry.
I was--

42:13.427 --> 42:16.706
I was just down the hall
about to make a phone call.

42:16.844 --> 42:18.087
You're under arrest.

42:18.225 --> 42:20.020
Now you can either
come voluntarily

42:20.158 --> 42:21.953
or I'll put the cuffs on you.

42:22.091 --> 42:23.610
Now how do you want this to go?

42:23.748 --> 42:25.232
Well, you see,
the thing is, Sheriff,

42:25.370 --> 42:28.856
that-that call
I was telling you about,

42:28.994 --> 42:32.032
it's to a man I know,
an old colleague of mine,

42:32.170 --> 42:33.689
Colonel Jack Hollister,

42:33.827 --> 42:36.036
US Army Special Forces Command.

42:37.520 --> 42:39.729
If I make that call and tell him

42:39.867 --> 42:42.145
about all the illegal activities

42:42.283 --> 42:45.493
going on
in your fine little town,

42:45.632 --> 42:48.635
and if I do that,
I guarantee within 24 hours

42:48.773 --> 42:50.913
this place will be swarming
with federal agents,

42:51.051 --> 42:53.571
not to mention
national media attention.

42:53.709 --> 42:55.607
If that happens,
I suspect you'll spend

42:55.745 --> 42:57.816
the rest of your career
in a federal penitentiary.

42:57.954 --> 43:00.267
[SCOFFS]
Now I gotta make the call,

43:00.405 --> 43:04.133
'cause if I don't, they'll come
looking for me for sure.

43:04.271 --> 43:08.344
But there is one other option.

43:10.070 --> 43:13.763
I could make the call
and just say nothing.

43:13.901 --> 43:16.145
Then I'd just have myself
one last cup of coffee

43:16.283 --> 43:19.113
and, uh, hit the road.

43:19.251 --> 43:22.082
[TENSE THEME PLAYING]

43:22.220 --> 43:25.326
So see, it's your call, Sheriff.

43:33.887 --> 43:36.406
[CLEARING THROAT]
Heh. Well...

43:38.236 --> 43:41.135
if that's how
you want to play it,

43:41.273 --> 43:43.137
I'll be on my way.

43:44.069 --> 43:45.070
Thank you, sir.

43:47.383 --> 43:49.730
[DOOR CLICKING]

43:52.975 --> 43:54.562
[DOOR CLICKING]

43:54.701 --> 43:55.874
Is any of that true?

43:56.012 --> 43:56.875
Not a word.

43:58.049 --> 43:59.947
[BEER SLOSHING]

44:05.263 --> 44:06.816
Hm.

44:06.954 --> 44:08.473
Quality beer.

44:08.611 --> 44:10.544
Exotic fruits,

